13 B. The Department of Public Safety shall provide administrative
14 support necessary for the Committee to accomplish the goals and
15 objectives assigned by this section.
16 C. The Committee shall meet at the direction of the chair, and
17 shall meet not less than once a year, but not more than four times a
18 year. A vice chair shall be elected by the Committee from among its
19 members. The vice chair shall act as chair of the Committee in the
20 absence of the chair.
21 D. The Committee is authorized to collect, analyze, and
22 interpret relevant crash data on impaired driving and associated
23 traffic crashes. In addition, the Committee is authorized to
