5 E. The Committee shall annually complete a statewide strategic
6 plan to reduce the incidents of impaired driving and impaired
7 driving crashes. The plan shall be submitted no later than December
8 31 of each year to the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the
9 Oklahoma State Senate, and the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
10 Representatives.
11 F. Members of the Committee who are otherwise employed by a
12 state agency or political subdivision shall serve without additional
13 compensation. Members of the Committee who are otherwise employed
14 by a state agency or political subdivision shall be entitled to
15 reimbursement for any actual and necessary traveling expenses in
16 accordance with the State Travel Reimbursement Act from the
17 employing agency.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
